   <div class='caption'>
       <p> 
      Screenshot showing RoadWorks' horizontal alignment editor.  The curve editing tool is
      pre-programmed to keep the alignment within design criteria set by highway agencies
      for maximum degree of curve. The topographic contours are color-coded by elevation
      to assist in visualization of the landscape; aerial photos can also be added to the view.
      The curves can be of either circular or spiral type. Spiral curves, because of their
      complexity are avoided by roadway engineers but are useful in sensitive landscapes because
      of their gentle transitions from tangent to curve.
    </p>
   
